<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  Entitlements for a Developer ID + Hardened Runtime build (NOT App Sandbox).

  Rationale (see docs/ARCHITECTURE.md and docs/DEVELOPMENT.md): Claudex is a local
  developer control plane. The app itself is a thin loopback HTTP/SSE client, but the
  toolchain it fronts (claudexd) spawns native coding harnesses and reads/writes arbitrary
  repos, which the App Sandbox cannot express. We therefore distribute outside the App Store
  with Developer ID + notarization + hardened runtime, and we do NOT enable
  `com.apple.security.app-sandbox`.

  Hardened runtime allows outbound network (loopback to claudexd) without an entitlement.
  Keep this list MINIMAL — add an entitlement only with a concrete, documented need.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!-- Intentionally no com.apple.security.app-sandbox key: this is a Developer ID,
         non-sandboxed build. -->
</dict>
</plist>
